    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Phenomena, appearances, or other results that are considered spurious because they do not necessarily represent a real biological, physical, or other structures or processes, but are instead created by the experimental technique or procedure itself.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
